modules.description: Provides functions to send HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2.0 requests, handle redirects up to a specified limit, and manage both HTTP and HTTPS protocols. Works with URL strings, request methods, headers, and body data. Used to fetch resources from web servers, interact with APIs, and perform network requests in applications requiring minimal dependencies.

Provides a HTTP client capable of handling requests over HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2, with support for both HTTP and HTTPS using OCaml-TLS. It establishes connections using the happy-eyeballs algorithm and can follow redirects during a single request. The module exposes types for requests, responses, and errors, along with operations to send requests and process results. Examples include fetching a remote resource, handling redirects, and inspecting response headers and body.
